    "name": "Lumina — Oracle V2 migration via TimelockController",
    "description": "Two-step Timelock batch executed by the Lumina Safe (0xa17e8b7f985022BC3c607e9c4858A1C264b33cFD). The Safe is the proposer+executor of the TimelockController (0xd0De5D53dCA2D96cdE7FAf540BA3f3a44fdB747a), which is the actual owner of CoverRouter. Because TimelockController.minDelay = 0, schedule and execute can run in the same Safe transaction. This batch wraps 8 inner operations against the CoverRouter at 0xd5f8678A0F2149B6342F9014CCe6d743234Ca025: (1-5) updateProductShield re-pointing the 5 active productIds (BTCCAT-001, ETHAPOC-001, DEPEG-STABLE-001, ILPROT-001, EXPLOIT-001) from V1 shields to the V2 shields deployed by DeployOracleV2Batch.s.sol; (6) setMaxPayoutsPerDay(10) circuit breaker; (7) setLargePayoutThreshold(50,000 USDC); (8) setLargePayoutDelay(86400 = 24h). Salt = keccak256(\"LUMINA-ORACLE-V2-MIGRATION-2026-04-09\"). Predecessor = 0x00 (no dependency).",
